This category of Mitigations describes a wide range of strategies and actions aimed at preventing the spread of contagious diseases in green building neighborhoods. These include improving surveillance and contact tracing to identify and address vulnerabilities, as well as resource allocation and proximity shopping to ensure access to essential goods and services. The list also includes measures such as school closures, stay-at-home orders, and border closures to reduce the risk of transmission. Additionally, there are strategies related to infrastructure, such as the use of robots, copper coating, and proper insulation for buildings. Mitigations also involve community engagement, open and consistent messaging, and targeted policies to promote public cooperation and awareness. Furthermore, the list features interventions that consider the connection to nature, such as habitat diversity and increased tree canopy. Overall, these Mitigations encompass a comprehensive array of measures to mitigate the spread of contagious diseases and promote the health and safety of individuals in green building neighborhoods.